@page "/help"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.Authorize]

<PageTitle>Help</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Help Guide</h1>
    <p class="hint">Quick reference for using the School Management System.</p>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>On first run, the app applies database migrations automatically at startup.</li>
        <li>Default <strong>Admin</strong> and <strong>Coordinator</strong> login accounts are created automatically if missing.</li>
        <li>Sign in with the credentials from your installer, then open <strong>Settings → User Accounts</strong> and change default passwords.</li>
        <li>Create teacher accounts under <strong>Settings → User Accounts</strong> and assign sections under <strong>Settings → Staff Assignment</strong>.</li>
        <li>Update school details under <strong>Settings → School Settings</strong>, then add classes and students.</li>
    </ol>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Default Accounts (first install only)</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Admin</strong> — full access including settings, users, backup, and biometric enrollment.</li>
        <li><strong>Coordinator</strong> — attendance across all sections, notifications, and academic years.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="hint">
        Teacher accounts are <em>not</em> created automatically. The admin creates them after setup.
        Passwords are not shown on the login screen — use the credentials from your deployment notes, then change them immediately.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Login Troubleshooting</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Use the full email address as the username.</li>
        <li>Passwords are case-sensitive.</li>
        <li>If login fails after a server restart, confirm SQL Server is running and the connection string in <code>appsettings.json</code> is correct.</li>
        <li><strong>Forgot password (offline):</strong> an admin can reset it at <strong>Settings → User Accounts</strong>. No email is required.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin locked out completely:</strong> your IT installer can run <code>scripts\reset-admin-password.ps1</code> on the school server. Full steps: <strong>docs/DEPLOYMENT.md</strong> (section 8).</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Students &amp; Classes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Classes</strong> — create class names and sections (for example, 9-A).</li>
        <li><strong>Students</strong> — add student records and map each student’s biometric user ID for gate scans.</li>
        <li><strong>Promote Students</strong> — move students to the next class at year-end or when sections change.</li>
        <li>Use search and pagination on the student list for large rosters.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Attendance</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Mark Attendance</strong> — teachers or admins mark present, absent, late, or leave manually.</li>
        <li><strong>Daily Sheet</strong> — review and finalize the day’s attendance summary.</li>
        <li><strong>Holiday Calendar</strong> — one-time holidays (Eid, exams) or annual repeating holidays (14 Aug, 25 Dec).</li>
        <li><strong>Attendance Gate</strong> — phone/tablet kiosk with face scan (HTTPS required on mobile).</li>
        <li><strong>Live Gate</strong> — monitor biometric IN/OUT events in real time.</li>
        <li><strong>Local Biometric Test</strong> — enroll faces and test scans (admin only).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="hint">
        School start time and late grace are configured in School Settings.
        First scan of the day = IN; second scan = OUT. Enroll each student’s face on the same phone used at the gate when possible.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Biometric Device</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Configure device connection (USB or TCP) under <strong>Settings → Biometric Device</strong>.</li>
        <li>Ensure each student’s biometric user ID matches the ID stored on the device.</li>
        <li>The background worker polls enabled devices and records attendance automatically.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Database Backup (Admin)</h2>
    <p>
        Admins can create a manual SQL Server backup from <strong>Settings → Database Backup</strong>.
        Backups are saved as <code>.bak</code> files that you can download from the same page.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Click <strong>Create Backup Now</strong> before major changes or end-of-term archiving.</li>
        <li>Store downloaded backup files securely off-site (USB drive, cloud storage, or another server).</li>
        <li>To restore, use SQL Server Management Studio or <code>RESTORE DATABASE</code> with the downloaded <code>.bak</code> file.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="hint">
        Backups are stored under <code>App_Data/backups</code> on the school server (SQL Express on Windows).
        The SQL service account needs write permission on that folder. See <strong>docs/DEPLOYMENT.md</strong>.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Holidays &amp; Off Days</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Weekly off</strong> — Settings → School Settings → Recurring Weekly Off Days (e.g. every Sunday).</li>
        <li><strong>Annual holiday</strong> — Attendance → Holiday Calendar → check “Repeat every year” (e.g. 14 Aug, 25 Dec).</li>
        <li><strong>One-time holiday</strong> — same calendar, leave “Repeat every year” unchecked (e.g. Eid, exam day).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="hint">Lunar holidays like Eid change each year — mark them once per year without the annual repeat option.</p>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Parent notifications (WhatsApp)</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Enable each alert type under <strong>Settings → School Settings</strong> (check-in, check-out, late, absent, present, leave).</li>
        <li>Messages are queued on <strong>Attendance → Parent Notifications</strong>. Open each WhatsApp link to send to the parent number on the student record.</li>
        <li>Gate scans queue check-in or check-out (late scans send the late message). Manual attendance queues a message when the status changes.</li>
        <li>End-of-day finalize still queues absent alerts for students with no attendance record.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Roles</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Admin</strong> — full access including settings, users, promotion, backup, and face enrollment.</li>
        <li><strong>Coordinator</strong> — attendance, notifications, academic years, gate, and live monitor.</li>
        <li><strong>Gate Keeper</strong> — gate kiosk only: scan attendance at the gate and view help. Face enrollment is done by admin or coordinator.</li>
        <li><strong>Students</strong> — status: Active, Suspended, Expelled, Transferred, or Left. Add a reason when suspending or expelling. Non-active students are hidden from attendance and gate; use Students → <strong>Non-active only</strong> to find them.</li>
        <li><strong>Suspended</strong> — temporary (e.g. 1–2 weeks discipline, fees hold, parent request). Example note: <em>Suspended 2 weeks for fighting — review 15 Jul</em>. Set back to <strong>Active</strong> when they return.</li>
        <li><strong>Expelled</strong> — permanent removal (e.g. serious misconduct, repeated violations). Example note: <em>Expelled by committee — cheating, 10 Jun 2026</em>. Reason is required.</li>
        <li><strong>Left</strong> — voluntary exit, not punishment (e.g. family moved, withdrew admission, completed and left). Example note: <em>Family relocated — withdrawn Mar 2026</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>Staff attendance</strong> — Attendance → Staff Attendance (admin/coordinator). Mark teachers and staff present, absent, late, or leave.</li>
        <li><strong>Teacher</strong> — student attendance and students for assigned sections only (created by admin).</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card help-section">
    <h2>Support</h2>
    <p>
        For technical issues, note the error message, the page you were on, and the time it occurred.
        Check the server logs when running on IIS or with <code>dotnet run</code> during setup.
    </p>
</div>
